# Source patches whose release effect ships via the Mono.Cecil transplant
# (Optimum.Patcher/Program.cs), not via a recompiled VintagestoryLib.dll.
# check-patches.sh checks these against build/ (the donor) same as any other
# patch, reverse-apply proves the donor source carries the change, but reports
# them under their own "cecil" counter instead of the ordinary applied/pending
# split. A patch on this list that fails reverse-apply is still a conflict:
# the list changes what a passing patch is called, not whether it passes.
#
# check-patches.sh cross-checks this list against Program.cs's own target,
# member-injection, and IL-hook type lists and fails loud on drift in either
# direction, so keep the two in sync by hand when Program.cs changes.
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/SystemRenderEntities.cs.patch
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/HudEntityNameTags.cs.patch
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/ChunkRenderer.cs.patch
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/ClientMain.cs.patch
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/SystemRenderPlayerEffects.cs.patch
patches/VintagestoryLib/Vintagestory.Client.NoObf/ClientPlatformWindows.cs.patch
